{
  "stem": "9899.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Being as young as we were and thinking that this is the way that life is, as I speak to you here, I-- to me, this is normal.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is my environment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I'd begun to believe that this was a normal environment for children to be in and for people to live in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Chaos had-- had become the daily fare, like it had become normal for me to stand in line every morning for a piece of bread for me to eat and a cup of water.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was all we were able to eat day in and day out in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They fed you once a day?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Once a day.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no more.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These were the rations that we were entitled to.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes my mother was able-- she left the ghetto to scrounge up a little bit more food, but very, very seldom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So for me, this was the normal way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And slowly, I kept asking, where is aunt this one or uncle the other, where they were not coming back?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were killed at the [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Janowska ?] prison.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of the brothers of my mother were killed at the [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Janowska ?] concentration camp, on my mother's family and on my father's family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some of there were simply shot on the street, and other were started to be carted off to the trains that took them to Treblinka, to Majdanek, and to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They still had no plans for the children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But soon they decided that it was time-- and it was 1942-- that the children were a hindrance, and they would live or survive maybe and continue the race.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had orders now to exterminate the Jewish race altogether.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
